[["/html[1]/body[1]/main[1]/div[4]/article[1]/div[1]/div[2]/div[1]/div[3]/div[1]/p[1]/text()[1]"," A 6-year-old boy and an 11-year-old boy were arrested Friday afternoon in New Orleans after they allegedly threatened a man with a gun. "],["/html[1]/body[1]/main[1]/div[4]/article[1]/div[1]/div[2]/div[1]/div[3]/div[1]/text()[2]","\n                \n              \n                    "],["/html[1]/body[1]/main[1]/div[4]/article[1]/div[1]/div[2]/div[1]/div[3]/div[1]/p[2]/text()[1]"," The man told police the boys began yelling obscenities at him as he approached them while they rummaged through the bed of a parked truck, the New Orleans Police Department said in a statement. "],["/html[1]/body[1]/main[1]/div[4]/article[1]/div[1]/div[2]/div[1]/div[3]/div[1]/text()[3]","\n                \n              \n                    "],["/html[1]/body[1]/main[1]/div[4]/article[1]/div[1]/div[2]/div[1]/div[3]/div[1]/p[3]/text()[1]"," The man said the older boy pulled a gun from his waistband and threatened to shoot him if he didn't leave the pair alone, according to police. "],["/html[1]/body[1]/main[1]/div[4]/article[1]/div[1]/div[2]/div[1]/div[3]/div[1]/text()[4]","\n                \n              \n                    "],["/html[1]/body[1]/main[1]/div[4]/article[1]/div[1]/div[2]/div[1]/div[3]/div[1]/p[4]/text()[1]"," The boys were arrested after a tip from a witness, and booked into the Juvenile Division for aggravated assault and illegal possession of a firearm by a juvenile, police said. "]]